ian Function Of Music -- tNotes On Contributors -- tWorks Cited -- tIndex Of Films Cited -- tIndex Of Names0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis groundbreaking collection by the most distinguished musicologists and film scholars in their fields gives long overdue recognition to music as equal to the image in shaping the experience of film. Refuting the familiar idea that music serves as an unnoticed prop for narrative, these essays demonstrate that music is a fully imagined and active power in the worlds of film. Even where films do give it a supporting role—and many do much more—music makes an independent contribution. Drawing on recent advances in musicology and cinema studies, Beyond the Soundtrack interprets the cinematic representation of music with unprecedented richness. The authors cover a broad range of narrative films, from the "silent" era (not so silent) to the present. Once we think beyond the soundtrack, this volume shows, there is no unheard music in cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMotion picture musicxHistory and criticism. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aaudio arts.  abeethoven.  acinema.  acultural capital.  adiegetic sound.  aentertainment industry.  aerotica.  afilm music.  afilm studies.  afilm.  afitzcarraldo.  afolk music.  aindigenous music.  akoyaanisqatsi.  aliminal spaces.  amodernity.  amovie studies.  amovies.  amusic and cartoons.  amusic history.  amusic in film.  amusic theory.  amusical agency.  amusical identity.  amusical meaning.  amusicology.  anondiegetic sound.  aphonoplay.  asilent films.  asymphonic score.  athe pianist.  athe piano.  avisual arts.1 aAltman, Rick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g